1
00:01:20,246 --> 00:01:23,281
NARRATOR:
Outside of the world you know,

2
00:01:23,349 --> 00:01:29,021
<i>there exists</i>
<i>the Realm Eternal: Asgard.</i>

3
00:01:29,089 --> 00:01:33,007
<i>The shining light of</i>
<i>the Nine Worlds,</i>

4
00:01:33,059 --> 00:01:36,996
<i>Asgard is home to the gods...</i>

5
00:01:39,799 --> 00:01:43,268
<i>all of whom bow down</i>
<i>before the All-Father...</i>

6
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:47,673
<i>Odin.</i>

7
00:01:47,741 --> 00:01:51,343
<i>Odin's lifeblood</i>
<i>flows through Asgard,</i>

8
00:01:51,410 --> 00:01:54,412
<i>and Asgard is Odin.</i>

9
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:56,698
<i>His power is all,</i>

10
00:01:56,766 --> 00:02:00,235
<i>and he keeps</i>
<i>the Asgardian realm safe.</i>

11
00:02:00,302 --> 00:02:04,556
<i>But once each winter,</i>
<i>the All-Father must rest</i>

12
00:02:04,624 --> 00:02:07,943
<i>and enter the Odinsleep.</i>

13
00:02:09,379 --> 00:02:11,279
<i>While Odin slumbers,</i>

14
00:02:11,348 --> 00:02:14,750
<i>his absence leaves Asgard</i>
<i>vulnerable...</i>

15
00:02:14,817 --> 00:02:17,353
<i>and this is when</i>
<i>the wicked</i>

16
00:02:17,420 --> 00:02:20,122
<i>descend upon his kingdom.</i>

17
00:02:22,024 --> 00:02:24,926
[#]

18
00:02:29,349 --> 00:02:31,266
Charge!

19
00:02:32,335 --> 00:02:33,635
[YELLING]

20
00:02:33,603 --> 00:02:35,771
[ALL GRUNTING]

21
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:44,530
<i>For seven days,</i>
<i>an onslaught of trolls,</i>

22
00:02:44,597 --> 00:02:47,599
<i>giants, dark elves and demons</i>

23
00:02:47,666 --> 00:02:51,370
<i>seek to take control</i>
<i>of the Nine Worlds.</i>

24
00:02:51,437 --> 00:02:56,842
<i>But they are eternally</i>
<i>defeated by him.</i>

25
00:02:56,826 --> 00:02:57,910
[GRUNTS]

26
00:02:58,077 --> 00:03:04,266
<i>My arrogant, oafish</i>
<i>brute of a stepbrother,</i>

27
00:03:04,333 --> 00:03:05,533
<i>Thor.</i>

28
00:03:05,601 --> 00:03:06,768
[THUNDER CRASHES]

29
00:03:09,339 --> 00:03:10,939
[GRUNTING SOFTLY]

30
00:03:14,443 --> 00:03:16,312
I don't understand.

31
00:03:18,247 --> 00:03:20,999
Where--? Where am I?

32
00:03:21,067 --> 00:03:22,967
[WHIMPERING]

33
00:03:30,126 --> 00:03:32,094
:
Hear me, human.

34
00:03:32,162 --> 00:03:33,395
You have been brought
to Asgard

35
00:03:33,463 --> 00:03:36,965
because in all
the universe,

36
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:40,835
only <i>you</i> have ever
brought near defeat

37
00:03:40,903 --> 00:03:43,605
to the Mighty Thor.

38
00:03:43,823 --> 00:03:44,723
[WHIMPERING SOFTLY]

39
00:03:44,790 --> 00:03:46,441
What?

40
00:03:46,509 --> 00:03:48,877
I-I-- I couldn't.
[GRUNTS]

41
00:03:49,112 --> 00:03:51,446
Not thee,
Bruce Banner.

42
00:03:51,514 --> 00:03:55,366
You are but a sniveling,
sad creature.

43
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:58,220
I speak of your other half.

44
00:03:58,287 --> 00:04:00,622
I speak of the Hulk.

45
00:04:00,623 --> 00:04:01,857
[GASPS]

46
00:04:01,992 --> 00:04:05,260
There is one day left
of the Odinsleep.

47
00:04:05,328 --> 00:04:07,329
The cycle is
nearly complete.

48
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:13,652
As always, the Asgardians
will emerge victorious

49
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:16,354
against the siege of darkness.

50
00:04:16,289 --> 00:04:19,641
My brother will seek
peace, and then...

51
00:04:20,794 --> 00:04:24,395
Then I shall destroy him.

52
00:04:24,464 --> 00:04:26,397
[#]

53
00:04:30,036 --> 00:04:31,703
[COUGHING, GROANING]

54
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:34,739
[BIRD CAWING]

55
00:04:37,994 --> 00:04:39,994
Verily, ye must say,

56
00:04:40,062 --> 00:04:44,132
that went far better
than last winter.

57
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:45,733
Tell us, Volstagg,

58
00:04:45,801 --> 00:04:48,403
are you going to dispatch
that troll beneath you

59
00:04:48,471 --> 00:04:50,839
or are you saving him
for dinner?

60
00:04:50,940 --> 00:04:52,107
[GRUNTS]

61
00:04:52,175 --> 00:04:56,244
That all depends on
how much mead I partake in.

62
00:04:56,312 --> 00:04:58,296
Did my ears
deceive me?

63
00:04:58,381 --> 00:05:01,032
Did Hogun the Grim
make a joke?

64
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:03,651
And here we thought
you were still in a foul mood

65
00:05:03,719 --> 00:05:06,271
because you didn't get to
slay a frost giant.

66
00:05:06,338 --> 00:05:09,190
I've still slain more than
thee, Fandral.

67
00:05:09,325 --> 00:05:13,128
But we shall see whom
the maidens reward more.

68
00:05:13,296 --> 00:05:15,096
[LAUGHING]

69
00:05:16,065 --> 00:05:17,299
[CHUCKLING]

70
00:05:22,805 --> 00:05:24,422
[CHUCKLES QUIETLY]

71
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:26,792
In mere hours,
the All-Father will wake,

72
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:28,927
and then we may rejoice.

73
00:05:30,947 --> 00:05:34,449
[#]

74
00:05:34,717 --> 00:05:38,686
The Lady Sif would know
what vexes thee.

75
00:05:38,888 --> 00:05:42,240
Aye. We won the day.

76
00:05:42,308 --> 00:05:45,427
All is well in
the realm of Asgard,

77
00:05:45,494 --> 00:05:47,930
but only until
the next Odinsleep.

78
00:05:47,997 --> 00:05:51,333
It is as it has always been.

79
00:05:51,367 --> 00:05:53,535
We must
learn to savor

80
00:05:53,603 --> 00:05:54,919
the moments
of peace.

81
00:05:54,987 --> 00:05:57,072
And accept the cycle
of death?

82
00:05:57,257 --> 00:05:58,874
How many of our brothers
and sisters

83
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:01,476
have fallen to this madness?

84
00:06:01,544 --> 00:06:04,329
Must we be chained
to this eternal struggle?

85
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:07,215
Be careful what you
wish for, my love,

86
00:06:07,317 --> 00:06:11,419
for when the cycle does break,
when things do change,

87
00:06:11,487 --> 00:06:14,289
then comes the end of days.

88
00:06:14,357 --> 00:06:17,091
Then comes Ragnarok.

89
00:06:18,361 --> 00:06:20,595
Perhaps our fates
are not ours to choose.

90
00:06:21,947 --> 00:06:23,298
But come.

91
00:06:23,366 --> 00:06:25,367
Let us return
to my father's palace

92
00:06:25,435 --> 00:06:27,369
and prepare for
his awakening.

93
00:06:30,106 --> 00:06:33,291
[#]

94
00:06:33,359 --> 00:06:37,412
Please, I'm begging you.
Don't do this.

95
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:40,615
I've fought all my life
to keep the Hulk inside.

96
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:43,885
You don't know
the destruction he can cause.

97
00:06:43,952 --> 00:06:46,221
[CHUCKLES]

98
00:06:46,289 --> 00:06:48,123
Don't know?

99
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:50,192
You fool.

100
00:06:50,259 --> 00:06:52,661
I'm counting on it.

101
00:06:52,729 --> 00:06:56,298
Look at you, so weak.

102
00:06:56,365 --> 00:06:58,667
Were it not for you
inside the Hulk's mind,

103
00:06:58,834 --> 00:07:01,169
suppressing his power,

104
00:07:01,237 --> 00:07:03,872
he would rule Midgard
with his rage.

105
00:07:03,940 --> 00:07:05,390
I won't let him out.

106
00:07:05,458 --> 00:07:07,842
I won't let you do this.

107
00:07:08,011 --> 00:07:10,345
You won't let me?

108
00:07:10,547 --> 00:07:13,682
How amusing
you mortals are.

109
00:07:13,683 --> 00:07:16,584
Now, let me see if
I recall correctly.

110
00:07:16,653 --> 00:07:20,155
It is anger that
unleashes the beast.

111
00:07:20,223 --> 00:07:22,023
[GASPS]

112
00:07:22,091 --> 00:07:22,707
[SCREAMS]

113
00:07:24,293 --> 00:07:25,861
[GRUNTS]

114
00:07:29,816 --> 00:07:33,918
I seem to have forgotten
the frailty of mortals.

115
00:07:33,986 --> 00:07:35,253
Look, Amora.

116
00:07:35,321 --> 00:07:38,506
I do believe
he's going to weep.

117
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:40,074
[GRUNTING]

118
00:07:40,142 --> 00:07:41,043
[GROWLING]

119
00:07:48,617 --> 00:07:49,668
[ROARING]

120
00:08:09,088 --> 00:08:10,672
[ROARING]

121
00:08:48,478 --> 00:08:49,594
[GRUNTING]

122
00:08:51,397 --> 00:08:53,214
[#]

123
00:08:59,455 --> 00:09:01,222
[GRUNTS, PANTING]

124
00:09:01,290 --> 00:09:02,390
No.

125
00:09:02,458 --> 00:09:03,725
No.

126
00:09:03,792 --> 00:09:05,693
It's impossible.

127
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,747
[ROARING]

128
00:09:18,541 --> 00:09:19,924
[GRUNTS]

129
00:09:19,992 --> 00:09:22,410
Now.

130
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:24,062
[GRUNTING]
[GROWLING]

131
00:09:27,366 --> 00:09:28,650
[GROANING]

132
00:09:37,993 --> 00:09:39,093
[GRUNTS]

133
00:09:40,362 --> 00:09:41,279
[GRUNTS]

134
00:09:51,290 --> 00:09:54,876
And so begins the end of Thor.

135
00:09:54,943 --> 00:09:56,111
[GROWLING]

136
00:09:57,430 --> 00:09:58,580
[LAUGHTER]

137
00:10:00,999 --> 00:10:02,216
[DISTANT ROARING]

138
00:10:04,554 --> 00:10:07,188
Yeah. What think
thee, Balder?

139
00:10:07,256 --> 00:10:10,591
One last troll with
dreams of conquest?

140
00:10:10,793 --> 00:10:12,594
Hmm.

141
00:10:12,662 --> 00:10:13,861
Perhaps.
[BIRDS CAWING]

142
00:10:18,167 --> 00:10:19,317
[#]
[GRUNTS]

143
00:10:20,469 --> 00:10:22,621
Come, Hogun, Fandral.

144
00:10:22,688 --> 00:10:26,290
Let us give unto this scoundrel
the gift of battle.

145
00:10:26,358 --> 00:10:27,241
[WHINNIES]

146
00:10:27,309 --> 00:10:28,759
Ha-ha!

147
00:10:29,828 --> 00:10:31,095
[ALL LAUGHING]

148
00:10:31,163 --> 00:10:32,596
Hyah!

149
00:10:32,632 --> 00:10:34,432
[#]

150
00:10:36,168 --> 00:10:38,303
Ha-ha!

151
00:10:38,388 --> 00:10:40,639
[ROARING]

152
00:10:42,241 --> 00:10:43,508
[GRUNTING]

153
00:10:57,473 --> 00:10:59,057
[MEN SCREAMING]

154
00:11:03,362 --> 00:11:05,847
[ROARING]

155
00:11:05,882 --> 00:11:09,684
The creature's power
is incredible.

156
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:11,086
Take care, Loki.

157
00:11:11,153 --> 00:11:13,221
My spell bonds you
to the creature,

158
00:11:13,288 --> 00:11:15,490
and while you are
master to it,

159
00:11:15,557 --> 00:11:18,259
I can feel him
fighting you.

160
00:11:18,327 --> 00:11:22,146
You have to listen to me.
It can't be controlled!

161
00:11:22,181 --> 00:11:24,215
Do not try my patience, worm,

162
00:11:24,282 --> 00:11:27,536
lest I turn
my attentions to thee.

163
00:11:27,703 --> 00:11:29,303
[GRUNTING]

164
00:11:33,141 --> 00:11:34,308
[ROARING]

165
00:11:34,376 --> 00:11:35,560
[CRIES OUT]

166
00:11:36,595 --> 00:11:37,696
Yah!
[GRUNTING]

167
00:11:39,565 --> 00:11:40,631
Oh!

168
00:11:45,337 --> 00:11:47,255
[#]

169
00:11:58,033 --> 00:11:59,134
[GRUNTING]

170
00:12:05,741 --> 00:12:06,974
[ROARING]

171
00:12:18,270 --> 00:12:20,589
[GRUNTING]

172
00:12:21,924 --> 00:12:22,807
[WHIMPERS]

173
00:12:22,874 --> 00:12:25,994
You are no troll, monster.

174
00:12:27,396 --> 00:12:28,246
[SOUNDING HORN]

175
00:12:39,675 --> 00:12:41,509
[HORN SOUNDING]

176
00:12:41,594 --> 00:12:43,378
'Tis Balder's horn.

177
00:12:43,512 --> 00:12:45,597
But this is
not right.

178
00:12:45,665 --> 00:12:48,049
Asgard's enemies
are all defeated.

179
00:12:48,116 --> 00:12:51,519
And yet the alarm
has sounded.

180
00:12:51,587 --> 00:12:53,187
Stay at Odin's side.

181
00:12:54,156 --> 00:12:55,523
Should I fail to
meet this threat,

182
00:12:55,590 --> 00:12:56,824
you must protect him.

183
00:13:02,064 --> 00:13:04,048
[#]

184
00:13:05,935 --> 00:13:07,718
But if Thor should fall,

185
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:10,204
what hope has Asgard?

186
00:13:10,373 --> 00:13:11,773
[HULK ROARING]

187
00:13:13,809 --> 00:13:15,309
[GRUNTING]

188
00:13:20,165 --> 00:13:23,101
You will have to
kill me, monster.

189
00:13:24,253 --> 00:13:27,021
For I shall not yield.

190
00:13:27,189 --> 00:13:28,890
[#]

191
00:13:30,259 --> 00:13:31,842
[THUNDER CRASHING]

192
00:13:32,928 --> 00:13:34,829
[GROWLS]

193
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:46,808
[#]

194
00:13:51,180 --> 00:13:52,780
[GRUNTING]

195
00:13:53,682 --> 00:13:56,651
Thor...the creature.

196
00:13:56,719 --> 00:13:59,987
Like nothing
I have ever seen.

197
00:13:59,989 --> 00:14:01,823
Aye, my friend.

198
00:14:01,890 --> 00:14:05,927
This is no immortal evil
that we face now.

199
00:14:05,995 --> 00:14:08,229
The Hulk has come to Asgard.

200
00:14:08,264 --> 00:14:09,430
[ROARING]

201
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:14,386
[GRUNTING, THOR CRIES OUT]

202
00:14:20,642 --> 00:14:22,076
Dr. Banner.

203
00:14:22,144 --> 00:14:24,145
Can you hear me
inside the beast?

204
00:14:24,212 --> 00:14:25,579
[GROWLING]

205
00:14:26,499 --> 00:14:28,700
[GRUNTING]

206
00:14:28,784 --> 00:14:30,351
Why have you come here?

207
00:14:30,419 --> 00:14:32,904
Why, to kill you, of course,

208
00:14:32,971 --> 00:14:34,672
dear stepbrother.

209
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:35,873
Loki?

210
00:14:36,892 --> 00:14:38,226
[GRUNTING]

211
00:14:42,231 --> 00:14:44,999
I have waited
an eternity for this.

212
00:14:45,201 --> 00:14:48,486
To crush you
with my bare hands.

213
00:14:48,554 --> 00:14:51,222
To match your might.

214
00:14:51,307 --> 00:14:54,476
To feel your life fade away,

215
00:14:54,543 --> 00:14:57,812
as my hands wrap around
your throat.

216
00:15:04,603 --> 00:15:07,505
[ROARING]

217
00:15:07,572 --> 00:15:08,973
Never!

218
00:15:35,650 --> 00:15:37,084
[GROWLING]

219
00:15:39,871 --> 00:15:40,922
[GRUNTING]

220
00:15:58,757 --> 00:15:59,723
[ROARING]

221
00:16:09,235 --> 00:16:12,837
Come to your new master,
Mjolnir,

222
00:16:12,904 --> 00:16:15,573
and let us smite
my stepbrother,

223
