224
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:19,093
for there are none stronger
than Loki now.

225
00:16:24,616 --> 00:16:25,633
[GROWLING]

226
00:16:29,371 --> 00:16:32,339
Rise, cursed hammer!

227
00:16:32,407 --> 00:16:36,344
Loki, enough. Your own
rage fuels the beast.

228
00:16:36,378 --> 00:16:38,379
I can feel the spell breaking.

229
00:16:38,380 --> 00:16:40,564
I will...

230
00:16:40,632 --> 00:16:43,767
have this hammer!

231
00:16:44,786 --> 00:16:46,170
[GROWLING]

232
00:16:51,393 --> 00:16:53,527
[#]

233
00:16:54,663 --> 00:16:58,099
Nay. You will have
its thunder.

234
00:17:02,221 --> 00:17:03,421
[SCREAMING]

235
00:17:04,539 --> 00:17:05,756
[ROARING]

236
00:17:13,782 --> 00:17:17,318
For Odin. For Asgard!

237
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:22,807
[ROARING]

238
00:17:24,610 --> 00:17:25,876
[CRIES OUT]

239
00:17:25,961 --> 00:17:27,044
[YELPS, GRUNTS]

240
00:17:29,264 --> 00:17:30,131
[AMORA GRUNTING]

241
00:17:30,199 --> 00:17:31,682
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

242
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,668
The monster...

243
00:17:33,735 --> 00:17:36,003
it is rage incarnate.

244
00:17:36,071 --> 00:17:38,306
It has shattered the spell.

245
00:17:38,373 --> 00:17:39,390
[SIGHS]

246
00:17:39,458 --> 00:17:41,209
The Hulk...

247
00:17:41,276 --> 00:17:42,843
is free.

248
00:17:48,651 --> 00:17:50,084
[GRUNTING]

249
00:17:53,255 --> 00:17:55,456
Will thou yield, Loki?

250
00:17:56,141 --> 00:17:57,258
[GROWLS]

251
00:17:58,877 --> 00:18:00,878
[ROARING]

252
00:18:04,199 --> 00:18:06,300
[SCREAMS]

253
00:18:10,238 --> 00:18:11,355
[GRUNTING]

254
00:18:13,608 --> 00:18:14,875
[LAUGHS]

255
00:18:16,778 --> 00:18:20,498
Truly, this is
the best of both worlds.

256
00:18:20,649 --> 00:18:22,466
I need not control the beast

257
00:18:22,534 --> 00:18:24,635
to enjoy its wrath.

258
00:18:24,836 --> 00:18:26,821
Goodbye,
brother.

259
00:18:26,989 --> 00:18:28,623
This...

260
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:30,091
This is not
what I wanted.

261
00:18:32,261 --> 00:18:35,396
There's no going
back, Amora.

262
00:18:35,464 --> 00:18:39,900
After all, if not for
your black, broken heart,

263
00:18:39,968 --> 00:18:42,236
none of this would
have been possible.

264
00:18:43,839 --> 00:18:46,374
[#]

265
00:18:46,475 --> 00:18:48,526
You don't know what you've done.

266
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:50,645
With no one
to reign the Hulk in,

267
00:18:50,712 --> 00:18:51,896
he'll tear down

268
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:53,530
your entire world.

269
00:18:54,949 --> 00:18:57,251
I find your prattling
useless, mortal,

270
00:18:57,319 --> 00:18:59,954
just as <i>you</i> are now
useless to me.

271
00:19:01,139 --> 00:19:02,356
[SCREAMING]

272
00:19:04,676 --> 00:19:06,177
[#]

273
00:19:06,345 --> 00:19:07,361
[ROARING]

274
00:19:09,848 --> 00:19:10,698
[GRUNTING]

275
00:19:17,039 --> 00:19:18,589
[GROWLING]

276
00:19:21,009 --> 00:19:22,643
[ROARING]

277
00:19:34,672 --> 00:19:36,523
[GRUNTING]

278
00:19:48,537 --> 00:19:49,670
[ROARING]

279
00:19:52,474 --> 00:19:53,657
[GRUNTING]

280
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:57,845
For Odin.

281
00:19:58,681 --> 00:20:00,547
For Asgard!

282
00:20:02,968 --> 00:20:04,384
[GRUNTING]

283
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:06,821
[COUGHS]

284
00:20:06,889 --> 00:20:08,756
[ROARING]
[GRUNTING]

285
00:20:36,935 --> 00:20:38,001
[#]

286
00:20:38,069 --> 00:20:39,419
[GRUNTING]

287
00:20:43,108 --> 00:20:44,875
[#]

288
00:20:45,961 --> 00:20:47,227
[ROARING]

289
00:20:59,140 --> 00:21:01,609
FEMALE VOICE:
Thor.

290
00:21:07,782 --> 00:21:08,749
[THOR GRUNTING]

291
00:21:15,157 --> 00:21:16,974
[GASPS]
Thor.

292
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:21,629
My love. I...

293
00:21:21,697 --> 00:21:23,064
I was angered...

294
00:21:23,132 --> 00:21:24,732
when you chose
Sif over me.

295
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:28,919
I did not-- I wanted
thy love, not your death.

296
00:21:30,088 --> 00:21:32,122
Please.

297
00:21:32,190 --> 00:21:33,591
Please come back
to me.

298
00:21:34,826 --> 00:21:35,876
Mm.

299
00:21:41,332 --> 00:21:44,318
[#]

300
00:21:44,420 --> 00:21:46,487
Amora.
- Yes, my love.

301
00:21:56,999 --> 00:21:58,666
Where...

302
00:21:58,733 --> 00:22:01,868
is Loki?

303
00:22:01,936 --> 00:22:04,505
[HULK ROARING]

304
00:22:23,158 --> 00:22:24,691
[HULK ROARING]

305
00:22:31,683 --> 00:22:32,900
[GRUNTS]

306
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:45,112
LOKI:
What is that monster doing?

307
00:22:45,213 --> 00:22:47,014
It travels
towards Odin.

308
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:55,373
[#]

309
00:22:55,423 --> 00:22:57,241
Loki.

310
00:22:57,442 --> 00:22:59,526
I would have words
with thee.

311
00:22:59,594 --> 00:23:03,864
No. You were at Hela's
door. I defeated you.

312
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:06,266
[GRUNTING]

313
00:23:09,421 --> 00:23:13,107
<i>You.</i> You dare
cross the god of--

314
00:23:13,175 --> 00:23:14,725
[CHOKING]

315
00:23:18,730 --> 00:23:19,830
[CHOKING]

316
00:23:31,459 --> 00:23:33,960
The Hulk will be sent
back to Midgard,

317
00:23:34,028 --> 00:23:36,279
and then you will
answer to Odin.

318
00:23:36,398 --> 00:23:38,282
Fine. Take the creature.

319
00:23:38,350 --> 00:23:40,334
It provided me
with amusement enough

320
00:23:40,536 --> 00:23:42,553
seeing it pummel you
nigh unto death.

321
00:23:42,621 --> 00:23:45,506
AMORA:
Loki, you--
You fool.

322
00:23:45,591 --> 00:23:46,540
You killed him.

323
00:23:46,607 --> 00:23:47,975
Do you know what
you've done?

324
00:23:49,411 --> 00:23:51,528
Because the mortal
died here,

325
00:23:51,596 --> 00:23:53,414
Hela claimed
his soul.

326
00:23:53,482 --> 00:23:54,549
Without his soul,

327
00:23:54,616 --> 00:23:56,350
I cannot return him
to Midgard.

328
00:23:56,518 --> 00:23:58,169
Without
Bruce Banner,

329
00:23:58,236 --> 00:24:00,754
the Hulk cannot
leave Asgard.

330
00:24:00,822 --> 00:24:01,955
[GRUNTS]

331
00:24:09,497 --> 00:24:10,564
[METAL CLANGS]

332
00:24:10,631 --> 00:24:11,599
[HORSE WHINNIES]

333
00:24:18,006 --> 00:24:20,040
[#]

334
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:26,163
[WHINNYING]

335
00:24:31,553 --> 00:24:32,652
[ROARING]

336
00:24:33,622 --> 00:24:36,189
Valkyries, warriors...

337
00:24:36,425 --> 00:24:39,493
your seats in Valhalla
are promised.

338
00:24:39,678 --> 00:24:42,763
Protect Odin
with your lives.

339
00:24:43,998 --> 00:24:45,533
For Asgard!

340
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:47,601
[ROARING]
[GRUNTING]

341
00:24:51,006 --> 00:24:53,974
I saw the beast's
eyes, brother.

342
00:24:54,042 --> 00:24:58,345
It will not stop until
all of Asgard is destroyed.

343
00:24:58,413 --> 00:24:59,930
Until Odin
is broken.

344
00:25:00,115 --> 00:25:02,883
You have brought
a new Ragnarok down upon us all.

345
00:25:02,951 --> 00:25:04,818
[GRUNTING]

346
00:25:04,886 --> 00:25:08,355
[CHOKING]
It's possible I made
a poor choice.

347
00:25:12,527 --> 00:25:13,794
Amora, I need you

348
00:25:13,861 --> 00:25:14,895
by Odin's
side.

349
00:25:14,963 --> 00:25:16,997
Protect him, along
with Lady Sif.

350
00:25:17,065 --> 00:25:18,265
[SIGHS]

351
00:25:19,784 --> 00:25:21,735
As...you wish.

352
00:25:26,024 --> 00:25:27,207
Loki,

353
00:25:27,376 --> 00:25:29,877
you will send whatever dark
forces you have left

354
00:25:29,945 --> 00:25:32,012
to battle the Hulk.

355
00:25:32,147 --> 00:25:36,517
Then you and I,
we go unto Hel this day.

356
00:25:41,122 --> 00:25:43,590
[#]

357
00:25:51,499 --> 00:25:54,251
Rest your weapon,
shield maiden.

358
00:25:54,403 --> 00:25:57,471
I have come to aid thee
in Odin's defense

359
00:25:57,639 --> 00:25:58,972
at Thor's
request.

360
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:01,608
His request, you say?

361
00:26:01,676 --> 00:26:04,277
More likely
his penance, witch.

362
00:26:04,345 --> 00:26:06,947
No doubt he saw your hand
in this attack.

363
00:26:08,750 --> 00:26:13,220
A punishment more cruel
than you can imagine, cow.

364
00:26:16,608 --> 00:26:18,775
[HULK ROARING]

365
00:26:18,843 --> 00:26:20,411
[HORSE WHINNYING]

366
00:26:24,682 --> 00:26:26,550
[GRUNTING]

367
00:26:36,611 --> 00:26:37,677
[ROARING]

368
00:26:39,014 --> 00:26:39,997
[GRUNTS]

369
00:26:40,064 --> 00:26:42,266
Loki, the god of mischief,

370
00:26:42,334 --> 00:26:44,417
bids you death,
mortal creature.

371
00:26:45,353 --> 00:26:47,187
[ROARING]
[GRUNTS]

372
00:26:50,108 --> 00:26:54,060
Long have I wished
never to see this realm.

373
00:27:05,991 --> 00:27:08,859
I always forget
what a busy time

374
00:27:08,927 --> 00:27:11,761
the Odinsleep is
for my daughter.

375
00:41:41,000 --> 00:42:31,000
<font color=green size=18> © MOSTOFA K@MAL™

376
00:27:11,997 --> 00:27:14,715
Dost thou see any newly
arrived friends here, brother?

377
00:27:14,733 --> 00:27:17,984
Have a care, Loki,
lest ye stay here.

378
00:27:18,052 --> 00:27:19,402
[GRUNTING]

379
00:27:24,475 --> 00:27:25,191
[SCREAMS]

380
00:27:26,294 --> 00:27:28,128
[GASPS, PANTING]

381
00:27:29,347 --> 00:27:32,099
Wh--? Where am I?

382
00:27:33,502 --> 00:27:35,969
[#]

383
00:27:48,817 --> 00:27:50,517
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

384
00:27:55,473 --> 00:27:59,292
No. It doesn't
make any sense.

385
00:28:00,795 --> 00:28:02,396
Huh.
- Bruce?

386
00:28:02,463 --> 00:28:03,430
[GASPS]

387
00:28:03,498 --> 00:28:05,515
Are you okay?
- Huh?

388
00:28:05,583 --> 00:28:07,601
Betty? Uh--

389
00:28:07,669 --> 00:28:09,703
I thought...
- Heh.

390
00:28:09,771 --> 00:28:11,721
I don't understand. I--

391
00:28:11,890 --> 00:28:16,276
I was alone, and then--
- You're not alone, Bruce.

392
00:28:16,344 --> 00:28:17,161
Mm.

393
00:28:17,312 --> 00:28:18,462
Not anymore.

394
00:28:22,049 --> 00:28:24,051
BOY:
Daddy.

395
00:28:28,206 --> 00:28:30,057
Come play with me.

396
00:28:30,192 --> 00:28:31,826
[WHIMPERING]

397
00:28:40,318 --> 00:28:42,485
[#]

398
00:28:47,442 --> 00:28:50,594
Hail Hela, goddess of the dead.

399
00:28:50,679 --> 00:28:52,879
We seek
an audience.

400
00:28:53,714 --> 00:28:55,915
[GROWLING]

401
00:28:57,352 --> 00:29:00,086
The sons of Odin risk much

402
00:29:00,154 --> 00:29:02,255
entering my realm.

403
00:29:02,324 --> 00:29:06,426
The Nine Worlds of Asgard
are in great peril, mistress,

404
00:29:06,528 --> 00:29:08,628
including Hel
and Niflheim.

405
00:29:08,696 --> 00:29:12,182
A new Ragnarok is upon us,
and we need your help.

406
00:29:12,250 --> 00:29:14,951
We need
Bruce Banner.

407
00:29:19,941 --> 00:29:24,244
The mortal's soul is mine,
Asgardian,

408
00:29:24,379 --> 00:29:27,247
as yours nearly was
this very day,

409
00:29:27,314 --> 00:29:29,716
and may well be again.

410
00:29:29,851 --> 00:29:32,786
You would risk everything
for the sake of one soul?

411
00:29:32,904 --> 00:29:37,057
Just as you would, Odinson.

412
00:29:37,125 --> 00:29:40,010
But you do not have
one soul, daughter.

413
00:29:40,077 --> 00:29:41,962
You have half
a soul.

414
00:29:42,030 --> 00:29:44,097
You have
Bruce Banner.

415
00:29:44,232 --> 00:29:47,300
You need the Hulk
to complete your prize.

416
00:29:49,621 --> 00:29:51,638
[HULK ROARING]

417
00:29:56,344 --> 00:29:57,978
[GRUNTING]

418
00:30:03,568 --> 00:30:05,018
[ROARING]

419
00:30:26,107 --> 00:30:27,908
[#]

420
00:30:29,043 --> 00:30:30,476
[SIGHS]

421
00:30:31,746 --> 00:30:33,313
Are you all right?

422
00:30:33,381 --> 00:30:34,748
I feel...

423
00:30:36,017 --> 00:30:37,984
I feel great.

424
00:30:39,487 --> 00:30:40,704
[SIGHS]

425
00:30:40,772 --> 00:30:43,523
I can't imagine
anything better.

426
00:30:47,561 --> 00:30:49,513
FEMALE VOICE:
<i>Bruce Banner.</i>

427
00:30:49,580 --> 00:30:51,131
[THUNDER CRASHES]

428
00:30:51,383 --> 00:30:53,417
[#]

429
00:31:03,945 --> 00:31:06,714
<i>Wake from this dream.</i>

430
00:31:11,569 --> 00:31:12,486
BRUCE:
Betty?

431
00:31:13,772 --> 00:31:16,523
Betty? Where are you?

432
00:31:19,493 --> 00:31:23,080
HELA:
The world of the living
has need of you.

433
00:31:23,097 --> 00:31:24,114
[YELPS]

434
00:31:27,218 --> 00:31:30,170
Who are you? What
do you want with me?

435
00:31:30,237 --> 00:31:32,622
Not I. He.

436
00:31:32,690 --> 00:31:36,960
Friend Banner, for
the sake of all of Asgard,

437
00:31:37,028 --> 00:31:39,279
you must become
the Hulk once more.

438
00:31:40,832 --> 00:31:41,815
Betty.

439
00:31:41,882 --> 00:31:43,700
Where--?

440
00:31:43,852 --> 00:31:44,651
Where--? Where's--?

441
00:31:47,789 --> 00:31:49,289
No.

442
00:31:50,725 --> 00:31:52,508
No!

443
00:31:52,710 --> 00:31:54,294
[ROARING]

444
00:32:01,202 --> 00:32:03,103
[#]

445
00:32:06,207 --> 00:32:07,807
[SQUAWKING]

446
00:32:09,043 --> 00:32:10,410
[ROARING]

447
00:32:23,558 --> 00:32:24,874
[ROARING]

448
00:32:31,299 --> 00:32:33,500
[MEN SCREAMING]

449
00:32:33,635 --> 00:32:35,235
[GASPS, GRUNTING]

450
00:32:37,638 --> 00:32:38,571
[GRUNTING]

451
00:32:42,277 --> 00:32:45,545
No. No, you can't ask me
to do that.

452
00:32:47,015 --> 00:32:49,599
I finally had peace.

453
00:32:49,751 --> 00:32:51,718
You don't know
what you're asking.

454
00:32:51,786 --> 00:32:53,237
Your time in Hel

455
00:32:53,304 --> 00:32:54,471
certainly has not
made you

456
00:32:54,539 --> 00:32:56,773
less of a worm,
mortal.

457
00:32:57,008 --> 00:32:58,408
[#]

458
00:32:59,677 --> 00:33:01,695
[GRUNTING]

459
00:33:10,955 --> 00:33:12,088
[SCREAMS]

460
00:33:15,176 --> 00:33:16,510
[GRUNTING]

461
00:33:28,239 --> 00:33:29,305
THOR:
Bruce Banner,

462
00:33:29,407 --> 00:33:31,758
I know thee to be
a man of honor.

463
00:33:33,027 --> 00:33:34,661
I know thee
to be a hero.

464
00:33:34,779 --> 00:33:36,813
The lives at stake
are not your concern,

465
00:33:36,881 --> 00:33:38,898
not even human...

466
00:33:38,966 --> 00:33:41,068
but I ask you anyway.

467
00:33:41,135 --> 00:33:42,852
Be that hero now.

468
00:33:47,274 --> 00:33:49,343
No.

469
00:33:49,410 --> 00:33:50,644
I can't.

470
00:33:50,795 --> 00:33:52,078
SIF:
Die, beast.

471
00:33:53,782 --> 00:33:54,798
[SCREAMS]
[GRUNTING]

472
00:34:02,857 --> 00:34:03,973
The Hulk's
soul is

473
00:34:04,041 --> 00:34:05,892
rightfully
yours, daughter.

474
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:09,012
Take it. Bring
the Hulk to Hel.

475
00:34:08,997 --> 00:34:12,031
Merge the two halves
of his soul...

476
00:34:12,099 --> 00:34:13,633
and claim him.

477
00:34:24,028 --> 00:34:25,845
[ROARING]

478
00:34:29,400 --> 00:34:31,217
HELA:
Bruce Banner,

479
00:34:31,285 --> 00:34:33,186
I will not force you
to forsake

480
00:34:33,254 --> 00:34:35,772
the rewards
of the afterlife.

481
00:34:35,940 --> 00:34:37,891
But you must be whole.

482
00:34:37,992 --> 00:34:40,961
No. I won't!

483
00:34:41,062 --> 00:34:43,396
You don't
understand.

484
00:34:45,950 --> 00:34:48,035
[ROARING]

485
00:34:52,055 --> 00:34:53,240
[GRUNTING]

486
00:34:54,259 --> 00:34:55,725
No!

487
00:34:59,297 --> 00:35:00,397
[SCREAMING]

488
00:35:00,465 --> 00:35:02,349
[ROARING]

489
00:35:05,587 --> 00:35:06,520
Mm?

490
00:35:14,879 --> 00:35:16,129
[GRUNTING]

491
00:35:18,933 --> 00:35:21,034
[#]

492
00:35:22,019 --> 00:35:22,936
[HULK GRUNTING]

493
00:35:39,436 --> 00:35:41,538
Curse you, Loki,

494
00:35:41,606 --> 00:35:43,273
for convincing me to bring

495
00:35:43,341 --> 00:35:45,725
this creature to my realm.

496
00:35:45,910 --> 00:35:47,160
Stay thy hand, Hela.

497
00:35:47,228 --> 00:35:49,062
We shall retrieve
the Hulk.

498
00:35:49,129 --> 00:35:50,347
"We?"

499
00:35:50,414 --> 00:35:53,183
The Hulk's fists have addled
your mind, thunderer.

500
00:35:53,318 --> 00:35:56,603
Fight with me, brother,
or die alone.

501
00:35:57,705 --> 00:35:58,671
Not much of a threat,

502
00:35:58,739 --> 00:36:00,724
considering we're
already in Hel.

503
00:36:00,791 --> 00:36:02,225
[ROARING]

504
00:36:03,912 --> 00:36:05,445
Have at thee!

505
00:36:08,983 --> 00:36:10,484
[BOTH GRUNTING]

506
00:36:23,264 --> 00:36:24,230
[SCREAMING]

507
00:36:33,557 --> 00:36:34,725
[ROARING]

508
00:36:48,855 --> 00:36:49,856
[CHUCKLES]

509
00:37:00,251 --> 00:37:01,668
My apologies.

510
00:37:01,736 --> 00:37:03,387
I was enjoying
the performance.

511
00:37:03,454 --> 00:37:05,205
[HULK GRUNTING]

512
00:37:08,176 --> 00:37:10,227
[#]

513
00:37:22,073 --> 00:37:23,356
[ROARING]

514
00:37:28,228 --> 00:37:30,580
Hulk!

515
00:37:30,664 --> 00:37:34,717
Let them go!
I'm the one you want.

516
00:37:34,785 --> 00:37:36,202
[ROARS]

517
00:37:40,508 --> 00:37:42,058
Come on.

518
00:37:49,283 --> 00:37:50,167
THOR:
Dr. Banner.

519
00:37:56,774 --> 00:37:59,759
[#]

520
00:37:59,826 --> 00:38:03,930
Hulk...tired.

521
00:38:10,822 --> 00:38:12,088
[PANTING]

522
00:38:15,226 --> 00:38:17,277
You called him weak,
Loki,

523
00:38:17,345 --> 00:38:19,729
but there is more strength
and courage in that man

524
00:38:19,930 --> 00:38:22,248
than you will
ever know.
- Hm.

525
00:38:22,316 --> 00:38:24,717
HELA:
This soul is too dangerous
to keep in Hel

526
00:38:24,785 --> 00:38:28,071
and too valuable to lose
to Valhalla.

527
00:38:28,940 --> 00:38:31,574
I will return him
to Midgard.

528
00:38:38,265 --> 00:38:39,298
[SPITS]

529
00:38:39,367 --> 00:38:41,801
Enough of this ridiculousness.

530
00:38:41,869 --> 00:38:45,305
To think that Loki,
prince of darkness,

531
00:38:45,373 --> 00:38:49,091
should waste his time
with defending Asgard.

532
00:38:49,327 --> 00:38:50,577
Nay, brother!

533
00:38:50,694 --> 00:38:52,312
We leave
together,

534
00:38:52,346 --> 00:38:54,614
for you still have
much to answer for.

535
00:38:54,681 --> 00:38:57,650
Indeed,
you both do.

536
00:38:57,718 --> 00:39:01,321
For today, Hela has
relinquished a soul,

537
00:39:01,456 --> 00:39:04,207
and she demands one
in exchange.

538
00:39:04,274 --> 00:39:07,210
You may try to
take my soul, death goddess,

539
00:39:07,277 --> 00:39:09,395
but I will make you
fight for it.

540
00:39:09,464 --> 00:39:12,315
And your realm has suffered
much already this day.

541
00:39:15,419 --> 00:39:17,604
HELA:
You speak the truth.

542
00:39:17,671 --> 00:39:21,074
So I shall take
<i>his soul</i> instead.

543
00:39:21,209 --> 00:39:22,225
What?

544
00:39:24,878 --> 00:39:26,112
[WHIMPERING]

545
00:39:26,197 --> 00:39:29,048
Thor. Thor!

546
00:39:29,033 --> 00:39:31,551
I helped you. I--

547
00:39:31,619 --> 00:39:33,219
[MUFFLED YELLING]

548
00:39:36,023 --> 00:39:37,107
I could fight you

549
00:39:37,174 --> 00:39:38,524
for Loki's soul.

550
00:39:38,592 --> 00:39:39,859
Will you?

551
00:39:39,927 --> 00:39:41,511
No.

552
00:39:41,579 --> 00:39:42,912
He is my father.

553
00:39:42,980 --> 00:39:45,582
His stay will
<i>not</i> be eternal.

554
00:39:45,650 --> 00:39:48,468
But know this,
Odinson.

555
00:39:48,535 --> 00:39:51,570
Your soul will be mine.

556
00:39:51,672 --> 00:39:54,791
And I will keep it
forever.

557
00:39:54,892 --> 00:39:58,077
Your fate
is inescapable.

558
00:39:58,145 --> 00:40:00,063
We shall see.

559
00:40:08,856 --> 00:40:11,724
[#]

560
00:40:36,867 --> 00:40:40,153
Thus, the cycle begins anew.

561
00:40:40,220 --> 00:40:43,189
Asgard is safe once again,

562
00:40:43,257 --> 00:40:46,059
defended to the end
by its heroes.

563
00:40:46,127 --> 00:40:49,396
I am proud of each of you
that stand before me.

564
00:40:49,463 --> 00:40:53,399
The day was saved by loyalty
and sacrifice.

565
00:40:53,467 --> 00:40:57,253
<i>We honor those</i>
<i>who fought beside us,</i>

566
00:40:57,321 --> 00:41:00,924
<i>those who are no longer</i>
<i>with us.</i>

567
00:41:01,025 --> 00:41:04,961
<i>And we defy those who would</i>
<i>see us brought to ruin.</i>

568
00:41:06,747 --> 00:41:08,665
And while the rewards
of Valhalla

569
00:41:08,732 --> 00:41:11,367
await all of Asgard's heroes,

570
00:41:11,435 --> 00:41:15,037
this day we honor
a hero of Midgard.

571
00:41:15,172 --> 00:41:17,474
A mortal who
sacrificed everything

572
00:41:17,541 --> 00:41:20,677
for a land
not his own.

573
00:41:22,412 --> 00:41:24,881
This day, a human
showed the gods

574
00:41:24,949 --> 00:41:26,883
what legends
are made of.

575
00:41:27,151 --> 00:41:31,070
Hail the mortal, Bruce Banner.